  "texts": [
    "A Stokes local system is a pair (V, Θ) where Θ is an irregular class at infinity and V is a local system of vector spaces on Σ(Θ) equipped with an I-grading (of dimension Θ) over the halo H, where I ⊂ I denotes the finite subcover corresponding to the active circles of Θ, such that the monodromy",
    "Stokes local systems yield a topological description of the category of algebraic connections on the affine line C = P 1 \\ {∞} (cf. e.g.",
    "Theorem 3.5.",
    "The category of algebraic connections on A 1 (C) is equivalent to the category of Stokes local systems (V, Θ).",
    "(We refer the reader to [Boa21, §8] for the definition of a morphism between two Stokes local systems, which is not completely obvious.)"
  ],
